remarks: Sent to B.M. 1937, by Mrs. Carson. Meon where the Titchfield-Stubbington road crosses it " when "excavating for the foundations of a small road-bridge"; he "came upon it about 4 feet below the surface of the river bed, a few feet from the downstream side of the bridge." This bridge is in Titchfield Parish, the bridge being in fact at the end of Bridge Street, Titchfield, which continues across it as the road to Stubbington.
